Package com.googlecode.ehcache.annotations.key

Interface Summary
CacheKeyGenerator<T extends Serializable> Generates a unique key based on the description of an invocation to an intercepted method.
 

Class Summary
AbstractCacheKeyGenerator<T extends Serializable> Base class for cache key generators.
DelegateCacheKeyGenerator AbstractCacheKeyGenerator implementation designed for subclassing.
HashCodeCacheKeyGenerator This key generator is a good option for fast but rough comparison of method invocations.
ListCacheKeyGenerator This key generator is a good option when you want to be 100% sure that two sets of method invocation arguments are the same.
MessageDigestCacheKeyGenerator This key generator is a good option when a secure hash of the arguments is needed or when a larger final key space is desired.
MessageDigestOutputStream Simple OutputStream that writes all data directly to the configured MessageDigest using the update methods.
ReadOnlyList<E extends Serializable> Composite interface that denotes a Serializable List that is read only.
ReflectionHashCodeCacheKeyGenerator An extension of HashCodeCacheKeyGenerator that uses reflection to generate hash codes for objects that don't implement hashCode.
StringCacheKeyGenerator Uses Arrays.deepToString(Object[]) to generate a cache key.
